content.description: Slopers while crouched on the right arete is the way to get this one started. Traverse up and left on good holds to the point.
content.location: Climber's right of Lip Gloss on the roadside face.

content.description: Starting on the tree stump, climb the steep slab to a couple of small pockets, then make a committing toss for the lip!
content.protection: A few pads and a spotter.
content.location: This climb starts on the tree stump, and climbs the slab between Raven and 14 Years.

content.description: Jump up to the flat shelf at about the 9 foot height; dead center in the face above the taggings, roughly 2 feet to the right of the small left facing corner. Campus up and left and mantle out on some less than comfy slopers.
content.location: Center of Hate Rock directly above the taggings.

content.description: Using the same start as Slap and Dangle, campus up and heelhook rightwards to better holds.
content.location: Exact same start as Slap and Dangle; dead center of Hate Rock on the shelf above the tagging.

content.description: To the right of the overhang, just above the "DJ Merced" tag, hop up to a small crimpy pocket that sits about 12 feet off the deck. Climb upwards and leftwards to a crimp and mantel onto the almost vertical wall for the lip. There are rocks sitting about to help get to the start if needed.
content.protection: bring a couple pads; the fall doesn't feel good :)
content.location: Right of the overhang on Hate Rock; just above the tagging "DJ Merced".

content.description: While standing, grab a solid hold on the roadside face's left arete. Head up and right on the arete to finish on the corner. For added dynamic good times, try tossing to the right arete from the start.
content.location: Around the back, climber's right of 14 Years. You will be on the roadside face.

content.description: Found climber's right of Cramps, start sitting with the obvious jug. Move your way up and left to better holds on less than forgiving rock.
content.location: Found right of Cramps; second route on Hate Rock.

content.description: A good start to the day on some rather unforgiving rock texture. Start with head-height edges to the immediate right of the arete. Using the crimps, make you way up and right.
content.location: When approaching Hate Rock from the lot, this is the first route you come across (left-most route when standing infront).

content.description: Sit start on the corner,find a small right hand sidepull, a left hand sloper and burst up to the arete for better holds. Finish slightly left on better holds.
content.location: Corner to the right of the tree stump on Hate Rock; right of The Raven.
